                            <comment id="17697081" author="emilles" created="Mon, 6 Mar 2023 18:13:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just a quick note, the static method is invoked if &lt;tt&gt;@CompileStatic&lt;/tt&gt; is in effect, in case you need a short-term workaround (besides calling the method directly).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17697085" author="emilles" created="Mon, 6 Mar 2023 18:24:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have not checked, but I&apos;m guessing the inverse was a problem for Groovy 3 and prior.  That is, &quot;new Test().testProperty&quot; was probably satisfied by the static method.  In Groovy 4, the isser gets first crack.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Update:&lt;/b&gt; Yes, Groovy 3 invokes the static getter for both &quot;Test.testProperty&quot; and &quot;new Test().testProperty&quot;.  Groovy 4 invokes the isser for &quot;new Test().testProperty&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17697156" author="emilles" created="Mon, 6 Mar 2023 22:04:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/f699f3a26692d1679b79d0b63a905c2eed9ff132&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/f699f3a26692d1679b79d0b63a905c2eed9ff132&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17697262" author="JIRAUSER299119" created="Tue, 7 Mar 2023 07:25:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the feedback.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sadly, I don&apos;t think @CompileStatic will help us, as we are interfacing mostly with Java-Classes, where the behavior is the same. If that makes any difference, I&apos;m sorry for not specifying this earlier.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17700008" author="JIRAUSER299119" created="Tue, 14 Mar 2023 07:59:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you very much! Works like a charm now!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
